DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("LimitedNumeric");

$int = random(1,9,1)*10+random(1,9,1)+random(0,9,1)/10+random(1,9,1)/100;

$ans1 = $int*0.1;
$ans2 = $int*0.01;
$ans3 = $int*0.001;

##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Calculate without using a calculator.

a.    [`[$int] \cdot 0.1 `] = [___________]{$ans1}

a.    [`[$int] \cdot 0.01 `] = [___________]{$ans2}

a.    [`[$int] \cdot 0.001 `] = [___________]{$ans3}

END_PGML

##############################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

* Multiplying by [`0.1`] is the same as dividing by [`10`];

* Multiplying by [`0.01`] is the same as dividing by [`100`]; 

* Multiplying by [`0.001`] is the same as dividing by [`1000`].

*Solutions:*

a.    [``[$int] \cdot 0.1 = [$int] \div 10 =[$ans1]``] as we move the decimal point to the left once.

a.    [``[$int] \cdot 0.01 = [$int] \div 100 =[$ans2]``] as we move the decimal point to the left twice. Note that we need to add in one zero.

a.    [``[$int] \cdot 0.001 = [$int] \div 1000 =[$ans3]``] as we move the decimal point to the left three times. Note that we need to add in two zeroes.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

